subSubSection.paragraph:
Dorsal and lateral surface of body covered by small granules or scales of varying size, on the dorsal surface interspaces with numerous slightly enlarged, weakly keeled tubercles (approximately three times the size of adjacent mid-dorsal scales); 
17
large tubercles in each paravertebral row between axilla and groin.

Ventral scales flat, mostly smooth, quadrangular, in 
10
longitudinal rows at midbody; lateralmost row of ventrals slightly elevated, ca. two-thirds size of adjacent ventrals, and not extending to axillary region; 
34
transverse rows of ventral scales between gular fold and vent, including two rows of preanals (two anterior preanals followed by three posterior preanals); lateralmost posterior preanal one-half size of the adjacent medial posterior preanal. Scales on surface of limbs slightly keeled and heterogeneous in size; 
38
total femoral pores; 
30
subdigital lamellae on fourth toe (five most basal divided by mid-ventral suture).
